  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: justify\">Forged from a hunk of skyfallen steel, there is a belief within the High Temple of Sigmar in Altdorf that this sword strikes with the force of Sigmar’s twin-tailed comet. A holy aura surrounds this blade, and its raw power can be felt from all Imperials as far as a town block away from it. It’s a subtle feeling—a tingling on the back of the neck, watering of the eyes or a tickling sensation in the palms. The more devout start having visions of the sword, and more than a few pilgrims have come snooping around near its resting place in Ubersreik in search of this artifact.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></p><p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: justify\"><strong>Weapon Type: </strong>Zweihander.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></p><p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: justify\"><strong>Ability: </strong>This sword has the <em>Fine </em>and <em>Unbreakable </em>Qualities since it’s forged from Meteoric Iron. The greatsword was blessed by priests of Sigmar and thus counts as Magical, and in the hands of Sigmar’s favored it gains the <em>Impact </em>Quality and increases its Damage by +3 against followers of Chaos. The blade gives off a glow of holy power. Creatures with the <em>Unstable </em>Trait engaged with the bearer lose 3 Wounds at the end of each turn.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></p>"
    },
